blog.description: Of course I came

body:
50 days of Andi Mack

Season 1 Episode 7: Dad Influence

  • “Mack, that is wack! Wackadacto yo, I mean, double wacker with cheese!” Ok, I can see why Cece isn’t a fan
  • I love Cece’s angry pruning
  • I’ve just realised how enormous their lockers are. I don’t know if it’s an American thing, but the lockers in my school are around a quarter of their size
  • Bowie’s car runs on used vegetable oil from restaurants? That’s actually pretty cool!
  • “Complete honesty doesn’t really run in the family” Well that was salty
  • Andi’s a pretty good drummer actually
  • I totally forgot Cyrus has asthma
  • Cyrus is such a good friend for helping Jandi even though he liked Jonah he is just too sweet
  • JB!!!
  • “I have put the ball in the tee, Andi just has to hit it out of the park!” What an adorable dork😂
  • “Let’s make like a cheque and BOUNCE” Well that certainly isn’t sketchy…
  • The bonding moments between Andi and Bowie were adorable
  • “That’s a ridiculous name for a sewing machine” “You’re a ridiculous name for a sewing machine “

summary: I hc buffy as aro  Especially after walkers fall formal thingy
question: I hc buffy as aro  Especially after walkers fall formal thingy
answer:
A valid head canon! I don’t agree with it, but it’s valid nonetheless. 

Personally, I just think that Buffy dislikes relationships - but I don’t think that means she doesn’t feel romantic attraction. I think that she always felt that attraction to Marty, but wouldn’t let herself feel it because she had so many walls built up. I also think she clearly had a crush on Walker, which may or may not have been romantic, but it just faded over time (likely due to the strain it was putting on her friendship with Andi). But that’s just my interpretation of the character!
